<p align="center" style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="6" style="font-size: 26pt;"><b>ValidFi: </b></font></font><font color="#7030a0"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="6" style="font-size: 26pt;"><i><b>Comprehensive Strategies, Institutional Quality Platform and User Communities</b></i></font></font></font></font></p>
<div><b><font size="6"><font face="Times New Roman, serif">Missions</font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi provides the most comprehensive financial and investment strategies based on an advanced quantitative platform. It supports user communities to discuss, educate and exchange ideas. With emphasis on systematic, holistic and precise step by step investment and planning strategies, it specializes in HOW while others specialize only in WHAT.</font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><img height="543" width="544" src="/LTISystem/UserFiles/Image/Guide_OO_html_43557712.gif" alt="" />&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="6"><font face="Times New Roman, serif">Overview</font></font></b></div>
<p align="left" style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">If you are a first time user, we strongly urge you to read the financial planning and asset allocation sections. These are the most important foundation for your success in financial investment. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Once you identify your overall strategies, you now could proceed to individual asset class investment strategies. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">The strategies ValidFi provides are based on popular institutional and individual level strategies found in magazines, books, academic papers and those proposed by users. </font></font></p>
<p align="left" style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">This guide could be used in conjunction with the demos we offer on how to use ValidFi platform. </font></font></font></p>
<p align="left" style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="6"><font face="Times New Roman, serif">Financial Planning</font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Many times, novice investors jump right into stock market or other financial instruments without clearly identifying their financial goals and risk tolerance. This is by far the most serious common mistake. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Financial planning has two major components: cash flow strategies and estate planning. Cash flow strategies are for your long term cash flow needs while estate planning is for your long lasting wealth. The outcome of the planning is a workable plan for investment portfolios with clear return and risk factors identified.</font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi offers a collection of cash flow investment strategies. The typical examples are the retirement withdrawal rate strategies in good time and bad time. Value averaging and dollar cost average are strategies on how to invest in the risky asset classes such as stock markets with a (planned) stream of cash income. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi plans to offer advanced cash flow planning and estate planning tools in the future. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><img height="435" width="523" src="/LTISystem/UserFiles/Image/Guide_OO_html_32800df5.gif" alt="" /></p>
<div><b><font size="6"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif">Portfolio Level Strategies</font></font></font></b></div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div><b><font size="6"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Asset Allocation Strategies</i></font></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Once a clear financial return and risk tolerance are identified, investors now could work on how to construct a portfolio to satisfy the goals. Asset allocation deals with how to allocate your capital into various asset classes. The allocation could be static or tactical (changes based on the outlook of the markets). Asset allocation strategies are probably the most important determining factor to achieve better risk-adjusted return through diversification across major and minor asset classes or strategies: according to </font></font><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asset_class"><font color="#000080"><u><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">a study by </font></font></u></font><font color="#000080"><u><font face="Times New Roman, serif">Gary Brinson, Randolph Hood and Gilbert Beebower</font></u></font></a><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">, asset allocation strategies is responsible for over 90% of variations in portfolio performance. Major asset classes include US equity (stock), international and emerging market equities, real estate, fixed income (bond and cash), commodities, hybrid (such as convertibles), private equity and/or hedging funds (such as long short, market neutral, convertible arbitrage etc.).</font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Asset allocation strategies could be static or tactical. Static (or called strategic) means a fixed target allocation among assets (with periodical (or other ways) rebalancing). Well known static asset allocations include those so called &lsquo;lazy&rsquo; portfolios. Tactical means changing the allocation mix (such as overweight on US equity or underweight on bonds) based on current outlook of the asset classes. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">In addition to allocation to assets, ValidFi also allows constructing portfolios based on multiple strategies, thus achieving further diversification.</font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Tutorials: </b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">The Asset Allocation Strategies section has a collection of tutorials in texts and videos on asset allocation and portfolio construction topics. It also lists the strategies ValidFi collects here. Regular and latest updates are also offered. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Summary and Update on Strategies: </b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi collects many well known asset allocation strategies.  Classification, summary and regular updates could be found here. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="5"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Cash Flow Strategies</i></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Cash flow strategies are about how a portfolio is constructed to handle cash inflow (income stream) and cash outflow (spending or withdrawing). When cash is deposited into a portfolio, when and how much is allocated to an asset class could have material impact on the portfolio&rsquo;s return. Similarly, when and how much an asset is sold to accommodate cash withdrawal not only could have impact on the portfolio return but also on the life of the portfolio value. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi collects two cash investment strategies: Value Averaging and Dollar Cost Average (DCA). These strategies are closely related to other strategies such as portfolio rebalancing strategies. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">For a retirement account, there have been numerous studies on withdrawal rate. ValidFi collects some of the strategies and plans to offer many more as time goes. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Other strategies include target date funds or life cycle funds. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Typical measures for cash flow strategies are the Internal Rate of Return (IRR) and residual portfolio values after a period of time. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="5"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Portfolio Rebalancing Strategies</i></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">As times go, the original allocation percentages among assets change because of asset appreciation or depreciation. Techniques are needed to rebalance the allocation back to target allocation percentages are called rebalancing strategies. A good rebalancing strategy could help improve the portfolio return (ranging from 0.1% to 1 or 2%) while reducing portfolio volatility. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi collects both periodical (such as annual) rebalancing and opportunistic rebalancing strategies.  </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="6"><font face="Times New Roman, serif">Asset Strategies</font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">For each asset invested, ValidFi collects their corresponding strategies. These include strategies for investing stock markets, real estate investment trusts (REITs), fixed income, commodities, convertibles etc. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="5"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Equity Investing Strategies</i></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Equity (i.e. stock market) investment is perhaps the most popular and (many times) chaotic and confusing. Investment strategies range from no strategy (i.e. impulse or emotional, which believe or not, might be the most popular and most dangerous) to buy and hold to trading as frequent as day trade. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi provides strategies based on valuation (such as S&amp;P price earning ratio), technical/timing (especially momentum) and various others utilizing mutual funds and closed end funds. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">At this moment, ValidFi only provides those based on mutual funds, ETFs and closed end funds. We are planning on offering individual stock investment strategies in the future. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="5"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Fixed Income Strategies</i></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Fixed income (or debt) investment is one of the second most important asset classes (in addition to equity). It plays key roles in reducing portfolio risk while enhancing income stream or even return. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi collects various strategies based on mutual funds and closed end funds. Quite interestingly, technical trading could be useful in this asset investment too. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="5"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Commodities Strategies</i></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Commodities investment has been long an area where only very special professional (so called managed future investment) could access. Recently, this asset class has drawn intensive interests and research has indicated that allocating certain percentages in this asset would achieve better returns while reducing risk. Furthermore, with introduction of various ETFs/ETNs and some mutual funds specializing in commodities, it is much easier for investors to get exposure on this asset class now.</font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">The popular and sometimes fascinating gold or gold bugs investing belong to this class.  </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">The most popular strategies in commodities investing are technical factor based. ValidFi collects several well known strategies in this class including Turtle Trading System and S&amp;P CTI. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="5"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Real Estate Strategies</i></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">REITs (or Real Estate Investment Trusts) are the most effective way to get exposure to this asset class. They are publically traded liquid securities. Even though with the bust of the recent real estate bubble, REIT investing represents one of the key asset classes investors should not ignore. </font></font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi offers some of the strategies in this class including technical and fundamental (yield based). </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="5"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><i>Hedging Strategies</i></font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">With introduction of mutual funds specializing hedging such as long short, option covered call based etc, hedging equity or other asset classes becomes an important category in ValidFi&rsquo;s strategy collection. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi currently offers techniques to invest based on fund selection. We plan to offer more strategies once options and futures are supported in the system. </font></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<div><b><font size="6"><font face="Times New Roman, serif">ValidFi Platform</font></font></b></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif">ValidFi offers an institutional quality platform for planning and investment strategies and portfolio management. Its salient features include:</font></font></span></p>
<ol>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Structured 	Portfolio Construction: </b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Unlike other stock/commodity trading systems, ValidFi treats portfolio level asset allocation, rebalancing and asset classes (which are commonly used in today's institutional investment practice) as first class citizens. It provides place holders for specifying portfolio level strategies, asset classfications and 	individual asset class strategies. </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Programmable 	Strategies:</b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"> 	a timed based programming language with Java syntax is used to 	construct a strategy. A strategy could be associated with several 	model portfolios. It could be also used for other portfolios. 	ValidFi provides rich APIs for manipulating the underlying 	portfolio and initiate buy/sell trading methods. It provides many 	technical indicators. Furthermore, linking to third party libraries 	such as the open source R is provided to access to powerful time 	series and statistical functions.</font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Local 	execution:</b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"> 	simulating a portfolio could be carried out in local machines to 	allow support of proprietary data and APIs. This reduces the 	slowdown for our central servers too.  </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Historical 	simulation of portfolios</b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">: 	back testing based on historical data for a portfolio with 	(multiple) strategies.  </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Portfolio 	statistics</b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">: 	Analytics of portfolios include MPT (Modern Portfolio Theory) 	statistics: The very basic goal of investment is to achieve good 	returns with reasonable risk. Popular statistics such as annualized 	returns, IRR (Internal Rate of Return), alpha, beta, standard 	deviation, Sharpe and maximum drawdown for various periods are 	computed. </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Powerful 	charting</b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">: 	The portfolio transaction log, other messages and the statistics are 	viewed through annotated charts.  </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Live 	monitoring of portfolios including trading signals: </b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Portfolios 	could be setup as &lsquo;LIVE&rsquo; and ValidFi will automatically update 	the portfolios based on the current markets. </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Hierarchical 	Portfolio Construction:</b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"> 	ValidFi also offers a powerful and natural way to allow a portfolio 	to be hierarchically constructed. An example is the Simple Core 	Satellite Portfolio strategy. This portfolio consists of two other 	portfolios and they in term are made of other portfolios. Multiple 	strategies could be developed and evaluated using this feature. 	Diversification not only comes as multiple asset class investment, 	but also as multiple strategies on those asset classes or even in 	the overall portfolio asset/strategy allocation. </font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><i><b>See 	demo here.</b></i></font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Statistical 	significance testing for investment strategies: </b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">confidence 	level testing is provided for rigorous study of the effectiveness of 	strategies. </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Mutual 	funds, ETFs, Closed End Funds (CEFs) and Portfolios screening and 	search: </b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">users 	could easily screen or search financial products or ValidFi&rsquo;s 	portfolios based on criteria such as alpha, Sharpe, discounted rate 	(for CEFs) and other key statistics. </font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><b>Up 	to date latest news and discussion feeds: </b></font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">ValidFi 	will automatically search well qualified web sources on any update, 	newly published books and papers on individual strategies. </font></font> 	</font></p>
    </li>
</ol>
