    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Black-Litterman 	Asset Allocation analysis tool: unlike a normal Markowitz&rsquo;s mean 	variance optimization method, this tool takes users&rsquo; outlook for 	the various asset classes expected returns and their confidence and 	perform the asset allocation optimization. Its output is much more 	stable and intuitive than the mean variance method. </font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><i><b>See 	demo here.</b></i></font></font></font></p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3">Markowitz&rsquo;s 	mean variance method: to be offered. </font></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font size="3"><i><b>See 	demo here.</b></i></font></font></font></p>
    </li>
</ul>
